</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-77_ pf-text-1"><strong>First aid kits</strong> - Maintain well-equipped first aid kits that are accessible within all child-centric environments.















</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-79_ pf-text-1"><strong>Policy development</strong> - Develop clear policies that outline the steps to be taken when a child sustains an injury such as a splinter.


















</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-81_ pf-text-1"><strong>Engagement</strong> - Engage children in age-appropriate discussions about the dangers of sharp objects and the importance of reporting injuries to an adult.



















</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-83_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-84_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-85_ pf-heading-1-h3">Conclusion
